12.13	Right-of-way_(railroad)	Right-of-way (transportation)	A right-of-way is a strip of land that is granted, through an easement or other mechanism, for transportation purposes, such as for a trail, driveway, rail line or highway. A right-of-way is reserved for the purposes of maintenance or expansion of existing services with the right-of-way. In the case of an easement, it may revert to its original owners if the facility is abandoned.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/Footpath_behind_Carr_Green_Cemetery%2C_Rastrick_%28SE138209%29_-_geograph.org.uk_-_135616.jpg/220px-Footpath_behind_Carr_Green_Cemetery%2C_Rastrick_%28SE138209%29_-_geograph.org.uk_-_135616.jpg
